added.title: Halloween
added.description: Raven tries to put the spirit of Halloween back in Halloween.

added.title: Campfire Stories
added.description: The Titans are having a terrible time on their camping trip so Robin suggests that they each tell a scary campfire story.

added.title: Scary Figure Dance
added.description: The Titans' Halloween party is interupted by the Hive Five robbing a candy factory.

added.title: Halloween vs. Christmas
added.description: When Santa tries to take over Halloween, it's up to the Titans and a few ghouls to stop him.

added.title: Costume Contest
added.description: Sick of losing the costume contest to the Hive Five every year, the Titans hatch a scheme to win.

added.title: Witches Brew
added.description: The Titans throw a Halloween party and invite the Justice League but the witches brew Robin creates has side effects.

added.title: Monster Squad!
added.description: The Titans want to be the scariest trick-or-treaters in town, so Raven casts a spell to turn them into real monsters.

added.title: TV Knight 5
added.description: Batman pretends to be sick to avoid work so he and Commissioner Gordon can run around town watching their favorite shows.

added.title: Yard Sale
added.description: Each of the Bears get offbeat items at a local yard sale. Their new possessions send them on their own separate adventures.

added.title: Nom Nom's Entourage
added.description: Nom Nom recruits the Bears to act as his entourage of friends. But when the Bears realize Nom Nom doesn't understand friendship, they decide to kick their day of bonding into high gear.

added.title: Losing Ice
added.description: Feeling unappreciated, Ice Bear leaves his brothers to be the chef of a restaurant. Desperate to fill the void, Grizz and Panda look for Ice Bear's replacement.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: Charlie and the Snake
added.description: Charlie is a solo guy who, like the Bears, would love to find a place for himself in the world. In an effort to do so, Charlie throws a party, but ends up going on an adventure with the unlikeliest of animals, a wild snake.

added.title: Hibernation
added.description: The bears, being an urban bunch, hadn't ever heard of the idea of hibernation until Chloe tells them about it. Grizz, loving the idea of eating a ton and then just sleeping to his heart's content, goes for it with reckless abandon.  But Grizz is so excited for hibernating... that he can't fall asleep.

added.title: The Ghost
added.description: Gumball must learn to say "no" when Carrie the Ghost uses his body against his will.

added.title: The Poltergeist
added.description: Gumball and Darwin give Mr Robinson a home and end up saving his marriage.

added.title: The Skull
added.description: Gumball and Darwin make friends with classmate Clayton, a compulsive liar who can shape-change!

added.title: The Mirror
added.description: When Gumball refuses to forward a scare email, the curse becomes all too real. Gumball receives a scare email from a freaky ghost and decides to ignore it despite Darwin's advice. He refuses to admit it but the curse starts to come true and his whole family gets dragged into another dimension. Gumball and Darwin, with help from Carrie, set out to save their family.

added.title: The Sucker
added.description: Gumball spends the day with Bomb Kid, who has decided Gumball is the perfect target for him and his friends to play pranks on. However he soon learns that Gumball is so gullible that pranks bounce off him.

added.title: The Spinoffs
added.description: Wishing to get rid of Gumball once and for all, his nemesis Rob offers up a variety of reality, action and comedy shows featuring characters other than Gumball. Unfortunately for Rob, each one is worse than the last.

added.title: The Stink
added.description: Gumball decides to put Mr. Small's eco-friendly principles to the test but it doesn't quite go as planned. Mr. Small disappears after deciding to leave the modern world behind. But on the plus side they discover that the Great Stink-Ape of Elmore Woods is definitely not extinct.

added.title: Super-Villain Team-Up
added.description: After a lull in alien antics, a restless Ben suggests to Max and Gwen that he might be a better hero if he went solo, but once Vilgax enlists the help of Zombozo to build a giant hypno-mechanism to hypnotize the entire world, Ben must rethink his strategy if he is to defeat the super-villain team-up.

added.title: Innervasion Part 1: Message in a Boxcar
added.description: As Team Tennyson prepares their boxcar for an upcoming race, Ben is hearing voices and is unable to go Upgrade to enhance his car, but once the race is interrupted by a mysterious Warbot, Ben must overcome the voices inside his head if he is to defeat the giant adversary.

added.title: Innervasion Part 2: Call the Dream Police
added.description: After defeating the Warbot and discovering Vilgax inside, Ben's "secret voices" only worsen and begin affecting his sleep, but once Gwen discovers a sleepwalking Ben using missing items from the campsite to create his own massive Junkbot, it is up to Ben to stop his own creation.

added.title: Innervasion Part 3: Strange Bedfellows
added.description: After the Junkbot shoots the Omnitrix and it begins glowing neon-blue, an imprisoned Vilgax explains it is now a gateway through which the Fulmini Empire will invade Earth, but the only way to stop them is from within the Omnitrix, so Ben must team up with the ultimate baddie if he is to save his planet.

added.title: Innervasion Part 4: Mind over Alien Matter
added.description: While inside the Omnitrix, Ben and Vilgax must work together if they are to close the gateway, but once the Fulmini leader, the High Override, appears, even that might not be enough. Luckily, help arrives in the form of a being calling itself Glitch!

added.title: The Filth
added.description: Ben is tasked with cleaning the Rust Bucket. But when he is tricked into letting the villainous and vile Fly Guys steal it, he must chase them down before they create an unstoppable maggot monster with sights firmly set on destroying Las Vegas.

added.title: Waterfilter
added.description: Ben, Gwen, and Max's trip to Niagara Falls is cut short by the horrid Hydromanders, creatures menacing them and their fellow tourists.

added.title: The Ring Leader
added.description: While winning big on a Sumo Slammers video game, Ben gets the idea to win a wrestling match for real until an intimidating wrestler named Iron Kyle decides to make it a true challenge.

added.title: Riding the Storm Out
added.description: Ben and Gwen's camping trip is interrupted by the emotionless Weatherheads (Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o) but a malfunctioning Omnitrix firing out a mishmash of aliens may not be the forecast for success.

added.title: The Clocktopus
added.description: In a peaceful coastal town, Ben must not only face the archaic antagonist Steam Smythe and his latest creation, the Clocktopus, but also his deepest, darkest fear: Squids!

added.title: Take 10
added.description: While trying to film his own indie film, Ben accidentally allows the Bug Gang to go free and when he takes the fight to their hidden lair Ben has to take on their narcissistic leader, the Ant Queen.

added.title: Fall Anthology
added.description: In an attempt to finish a school project, Craig remembers some of his favorite Fall moments.

added.title: Afterschool Snackdown
added.description: Craig enters a food competition in the Creek but worries he may be out of his league.

added.title: Creature Feature
added.description: Craig finds himself being chased by a monster in the Creek that's straight out of the movies!

added.title: King of Camping
added.description: The Williams Family goes camping and Craig helps his dad prove he's the King of Camping.

added.title: Lost in the Sewer
added.description: Craig agrees to help The Sewer Queen map the sewers, but he quickly finds himself in over his head.

added.title: The Future is Cardboard
added.description: The kids meet an eccentric Cardboard Creator that invites Craig to help finish his masterpiece.

added.title: The Brood
added.description: Craig's determination to get his granddad a cicada shell causes him, Kelsey and JP to become trapped in their stump!

added.title: Pudding the Planet First
added.description: Chef accidentally cooks up a killer cyborg turkey in a failed attempt to get the kids to appreciate him on Appreciation Day.

added.title: Supply Mom
added.description: When Chef's mom becomes the supply teacher for a day Duncan replaces Chef's to-do list with one of his own.

added.title: Mooshy Mon Mons
added.description: After eating Chef's extremely rare and expensive chocolates Courtney drags Owen, Izzy and Beth all the way to the Norberian Alps of Fruffenberg to replace them.

added.title: Student Becomes the Teacher
added.description: Chef is knocked unconscious right before a School Board Evaluator shows up for a big review. Now Owen has to fill in so Chef doesn't lose his Teaching License and to ensure the kids earn the pony ride Chef promised for good behavior.

added.title: Beth and the Beanstalk
added.description: After having a chocolate bar confiscated by Chef, Beth finds herself in a parallel giant world and aims to get back her now giant chocolate bar.

added.title: Pinata Regatta
added.description: Izzy can't bring herself to smash a Pinata during the class' Cinco De Mayo celebrations. But when that unsmashed Pinata comes to life and spawns an evil Pinata Army, it's batter up.

added.title: A Dame-gerous Game
added.description: After Leshawna, Bridgette, Owen and Cody win a Hide & Seek competition, they're trapped on a private island by a jealous former champion and forced to play for their freedom.

added.title: Royal Flush
added.description: When the other kids fear Harold has accidentally flushed himself down Chef's fancy new toilet, they travel into the sewer on a rescue mission. But will they find Harold before the mythical Alligator King traps them underground forever?

added.title: Total Eclipse of the Fart
added.description: After accidentally swallowing her first loose tooth and fearing that means no cash under the pillow, Leshawna tries to capture the tooth fairy. Instead, she accidentally captures the fart fairy. This comes with great consequence.

added.title: Stink. Stank. Stunk
added.description: When a skunk comes seeking its annual revenge on Chef, Duncan sees it as an opportunity to get a vacation from daycare.

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park VI
added.description: In Regular Show's sixth installment of "Terror Tales," the guys gather in the house on the Dome and tell scary Halloween stories just like ol' times, only this Halloween, the stories have an extra terrifying, science fiction twist.

added.title: Stakes Part 1: Marceline the Vampire Queen
added.description: Finn & Jake hunt for a shadowy predator and Marceline asks Princess Bubblegum for a huge favor.

added.title: Stakes Part 2: Everything Stays
added.description: As the sun rises on her last day, Marceline recalls her long extraordinary life.

added.title: Stakes Part 3: Vamps About
added.description: Five foes from Marceline's past come back to cause trouble for the Land of Ooo.

added.title: Stakes Part 4: Empress Eyes
added.description: When one of her oldest adversaries targets the Ice Kingdom, Marceline rushes to Simon's rescue.

added.title: Terror Tales of the Park V
added.description: The fifth installment of Terror Tales finds Benson trying to spice up the park's annual Halloween party by renting a wish making machine.

added.title: Blank Eyed Girl
added.description: One very spooky night, Finn and Jake come face-to-face with an urban myth.

added.title: Ghost Fly
added.description: Jake and the tree house are haunted by a vengeful spectre.

added.title: All Your Fault
added.description: Princess Bubblegum sends Finn and Jake to investigate a message of distress from the Earls of Lemongrab.

added.title: Sky Witch
added.description: Marceline is on a top-secret mission tracking Maja the Sky Witch. When she loses the witch's trail, Marceline turns to Princess Bubblegum for help.

added.title: Daddy's Little Monster
added.description: Finn and Jake return to the Nightosphere to rescue Marceline and get to the bottom of what's making her act so crazy.

added.title: No One Can Hear You
added.description: Where are the citizens of Ooo?

added.title: Bewitched, Bothered and Bothered Some More!
added.description: Flonk hires the Warriors to make Witch Way change his brother Helmut from a frog back to human.

added.title: King of the Zombeez
added.description: Frostferatu hires the Warriors to rid his castle of Zombeez when Neddy and a power mad zombie-bee queen take over.

added.title: Ghosthaste
added.description: Vambre becomes enamored of a poltergeist within Ghost Magisword and Prohyas must save her before his sister becomes a ghost herself!

added.title: Mushroom Menace
added.description: The Mysterious Hooded Woman wants the Warriors For Hire to defend her giant pumpkin home from the dreaded Smashroom Mushroom, but Vambre and Prohyas can't complete their mission without help from Zombie Pumpkin Magisword!

added.title: Flirty Phantom
added.description: Lost in Transylberia, the Warriors come to a haunted house for help and meet a young ghost lady inside that wants to spend the rest of her afterlife with Prohyas!

added.title: Little Sword of Horrors
added.description: Prohyas grows a new Magisword from a tiny seed, but doesn't know that his Carnivorous Plant Magisword is a menace to Lyvsherian society until its too late!

added.title: Witchy Simone Ruins Everything!
added.description: Witchy Simone joins Witch Way, but Gateaux is the odd cat out so he hires the Warriors to break up Witchy Simone and Morbidia and defeat a mission that has King Rexxtopher hopping mad!

added.title: Transylbabies
added.description: A mission to babysit Snowmanpire babies in Transylbiria leads Vambre and Prohyas to attack the local monster townsfolk in misguided attempts to keep the Snowbabies safe.

added.title: Unconventional Dolphinism
added.description: Since Prohyas is taking Dolphin Magisword to the Dolphin Convention, Vambre asks Witchy Simone to join her on a search for the Narwhal Magisword, angering a deadly Sealdebeast guard that lures dolphins away from the convention in the process.

added.title: Charmed, I'm Sure
added.description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

added.title: The Vampire Strikes Back
added.description: Ben, Rook, and Rad Dudesman come face to face with the evil Lord Transyl, a vampire-like alien who can make anyone his loyal slave! (Introducing new Ben alien, Whampire.)

added.title: Blukic and Driba Go to Area 51
added.description: A mysterious Galvan arrives and demands Blukic and Driba to give back a super powerful weapon needed to stop a threat to Earth.

added.title: Malgax Attacks
added.description: Ben finally manages to rid himself of Skurd... just when he needs the Slime-Biot most.

added.title: Heatwave
added.description: Apple and Onion try to spread cheer during a city-wide heatwave.

added.title: River of Gold
added.description: Apple & Onion try to finish a story before the book disappears forever.

added.title: Falafel's in Jail
added.description: Apple & Onion must get Falafel out of jail for a crime he did not commit.

added.title: The Fly
added.description: Apple and Onion must rid their apartment of a fly or face eviction.

added.title: Pulling Your Weight
added.description: Apple and Onion join a gym to gain the strength of seven people.

added.title: Masters Never Quit
added.description: Pursued by a magma monster, Cole, Princess Vania, Wu & the Lowly arrive at a mysterious temple deep in Shintaro Mountain, a temple which was once a training ground for Earth Elementals including Cole's own mother, Lilly!

added.title: The Darkest Hour
added.description: Forced to flee by the arrival of Grief-Bringer, the ninja, the Munce and the Geckles take refuge in the Geckle Strong-Cave. But the bitter feud between Munce and Geckles threatens to tear them apart, just when unity is needed most…when they are about to confront the Skull Sorcerer and Grief-Bringer!

added.title: The Ascent
added.description: Cole, the Lowly, Princess Vania and Wu discover that the stone-mech is fueled by Elemental Power, and attach it to the mine-carts in an effort to blast their way out of the mountain to confront the evil Skull Sorcerer!

added.title: The Upply Strike Back!
added.description: Cole and the Upply arrive at the Skull Sorcerer's keep in the hopes of rescuing Lloyd and the other ninja. But in order to do so, Cole will need to retrieve his mother's fabled swords, the Blades of Deliverance, which are hidden somewhere inside the keep!

added.title: The Son of Lilly
added.description: The battle for the fate of Shintaro Mountain concludes!

added.title: The News Never Sleeps!
added.description: Lil' Nelson takes a job as a paperboy, which is more difficult than it sounds in a city overrun by scorching Pyro Vipers and an evil Serpentine sorceress.

added.title: Ninja vs. Lava
added.description: The ninja find themselves trapped in a pyramid and must escape encroaching lava to warn NINJAGO City of a new Serpentine invasion.

added.title: Snaketastrophy
added.description: The Serpentine attack on NINJAGO City is seen from an unexpected perspective - entirely in the style of a live newscast delivered by Gayle Gossip and her cameraman.

added.title: Powerless
added.description: The ninja rush to the NINJAGO Museum of History to recover a dangerous scroll before it falls into the hands of the Serpentine Sorceress Aspheera.

added.title: Ancient History
added.description: While Aspheera pursues revenge on the "Treacherous Deceiver" who betrayed her, the ninja make a startling discovery.

added.title: Never Trust a Human
added.description: A flashback episode tells the story of Young Wu and Young Garmadon meeting Aspheera and teaching her the secrets of Spinjitzu.

added.title: Under Siege
added.description: Having learned Master Wu is the "Treacherous One," the ninja find themselves under siege at the Monastery, trying to protect Wu from the wrath of Aspheera.

added.title: The Explorer's Club
added.description: The ninja must break into the Explorer's Club to obtain the second Scroll of Forbidden Spinjitzu, running afoul of the club's manager and irate club-members.

added.title: Vengeance Is Mine!
added.description: Aspheera arrives at the Monastery of Spinjitzu and confronts Wu, forcing one of the ninja to make a heroic sacrifice.

added.title: A Cold Goodbye
added.description: Having learned Zane is not dead, Master Wu prepares to go after him, but Lloyd and the other ninja take matters into their own hands and defy their Master.

added.title: Charlene Mania
added.description: When Vic attempts to have the perfect day off, the town's sudden obsession for Charlene gets in his way.
added.tags: vic and val - see it first

added.title: Old Man Teo
added.description: When Vic and Val are tasked to volunteer at an Old Folks' Home, Val becomes buddies with the oldest, crankiest person in Monte Macabre and helps him reclaim his youthful power.
added.tags: vic and val - see it first

added.title: Poacher Patrol
added.description: When Don bestows Val the responsibility of patrolling the lake, Val takes it too far and stops who he believes to be a poacher -- with disastrous consequences.
added.tags: vic and val - see it first

added.title: The Horror of Hook Mountain
added.description: Tygra takes Lion-O climbing up the peak of Hook Mountain to teach him a lesson about trust. But when they get trapped by a snowstorm and take refuge in a creepy cabin owned by the creepy Snowman - it's Tygra's ability to the trust that's gonna be tested.

added.title: ThunderSlobs
added.description: Tygra's feeling unappreciated by the other ThunderCats so he starts hanging out with Mumm-Ra and cleaning his Black Pyramid?! Whaaaaaaat?

added.title: Working Grrrl
added.description: Cheetara is the fastest living person in the universe until Monkian beats her in a race?! Now Cheetara has to find something else to be the best at and the rest of the ThunderCats have to find out how Monkian got so darn fast!

added.title: Kevin Party
added.description: Kevin is throwing a party, and Steven is invited.

added.title: Can't Go Back
added.description: Ronaldo spots something mysterious on the moon, and Steven goes to investigate.

added.title: Now We're Only Falling Apart
added.description: Pearl tells a story.

added.title: What's Your Problem?
added.description: Amethyst convinces Steven to take a day off for himself.

added.title: The Perfect Adventure
added.description: When Mao Mao gets hungry for the perfect adventure, Adorabat tells a white lie.

added.title: No Shortcuts
added.description: After struggling to keep up, Adorabat gets a cybernetic "Mega-Mech." But can fancy new powers make up for experience?

added.title: Ultraclops
added.description: Badgerclops gets huge to destroy a towering monster, but when he refuses to shrink down, the kingdom faces a new terror.

added.title: Mao Mao's Bike Adventure
added.description: When Mao Mao underestimates enemy and friend alike, it almost costs him the entire kingdom.

added.title: Breakup
added.description:
Feeling left out, Adorabat wishes Mao Mao and Badgerclops would spend less time with each other and more time with her. When she gets
what she wishes for and accidentally breaks up their friendship, only the secret of their past can bring them back together.

added.title: Last One There
added.description: When Unikitty accidentally invokes an ancient curse, the gang must beat Master Frown and Brock back to the castle before one of them literally turns into a rotten egg.

added.title: The Very Best Candy
added.description: The gang can't decide which of their candy is the best, so they turn it sentient and have it fight to determine the winner.

added.title: The Unikingdom Awards
added.description: Unikitty throws an elaborate award show for everyone in the Unikingdom, including Master Frown and Brock, but tensions rise when Frown fails to win an award.

added.title: Dos mentiras una verdad
added.description: Cuando Lloyd desenmascara y revela la identidad de Mystake, el Emperador Garmadon acepta a Harumi como su hija de la oscuridad. Mientras tanto, Wu se aferra a su fe al llevar a sus amigos hacia territorios Oni peligrosos esperando encontrar el nido de la Primogénita.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Two Lies, One Truth
added.description: As Lloyd unmasks Mystake for who she truly is, Emperor Garmadon embraces Harumi as his daughter of darkness. Meanwhile, Wu holds onto faith as he leads his friends into dangerous Oni territory in the hope of finding Firstbourne's nest

added.title: The Weakest Link
added.description: Lloyd turns the tables on Harumi to take his father's power away, and the Ninja learn what it takes to be a Dragon Hunter.

added.title: El eslabon mas debil
added.description: Lloyd le paga con la misma moneda a Harumi para quitarle el poder a su padre, y los Ninjas aprenden lo que se necesita para ser un Cazador de Dragones.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Saving Faith
added.description: Lloyd and his team plot to take control of the Oni Titan. Meanwhile in the First Realm, the Ninja fall into Iron Baron's clutches and an old master returns.

added.title: Salvando a Faith
added.description: Lloyd y su equipo planean tomar el control del Oni Titan. Mientras tanto en el Primer Reino, los Ninja caen en las garras del Barón de Hierro y un viejo maestro regresa.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Lessons for a Master
added.description: When Iron Baron forces Wu to retrieve the Dragon Armor, things don't go as planned. In Ninjago, Lloyd can only endure so much as he holds onto hope for the Ninjas' return.

added.title: Lecciones para un maestro
added.description: Cuando el Barón de Hierro obliga a Wu a tomar la Armadura de Dragón, las cosas no salen como se planearon. En Ninjago, hay un límite de lo que Lloyd puede soportar mientras se aferra a la esperanza del regreso de los Ninjas.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: Green Destiny
added.description: The Ninja finally return home and unite to stop Emperor Garmadon, forcing Lloyd to make a decision that will forever change Ninjago.

added.title: Destino verde
added.description: Los Ninjas regresan por fin a casa y se unen para detener al Emperador Garmadon, obligando a Lloyd a tomar una decisión que cambiará por siempre a Ninjago.
added.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

added.title: El Tonto
added.description: Darwin termina en la sala de detención con el Chico Bomba, que decide convertir a Darwin en su nuevo blanco. Sin embargo, el ataque se vuelve en su contra cuando Darwin le arruina la vida.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: Historias Alternas
added.description: Rob crea una variedad de programas y formatos derivados ambientados en Elmore para reemplazar a Gumball.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: El Hedor
added.description: El Sr. Small se vuelve salvaje cuando Gumball y Darwin exponen su hipocresía.
added.originalseriesname: The Amazing World of Gumball en Espanol

added.title: La fiesta de Kevin
added.description: Kevin organizó una fiesta y Steven está invitado.

added.title: No puedo regresar
added.description: Ronaldo divisa algo misterioso en la luna, y Steven sale a investigar.

added.title: Ahora nos estamos separando
added.description: Perla cuenta una historia.

added.title: Cual es tu problema
added.description: Amatista convence a Steven de que se tome un día libre.

added.title: Cool Guy Clarence
added.description: When Clarence meets JT, the kid who mows their lawn, he finds a fast friend who shows him some cool new music, a new outlook on life and a sweet rat-tail! Clarence leans into the rat tail lifestyle, discovering a whole new side of Aberdale he never knew existed.

added.title: Big Trouble in Little Aberdale
added.description: After stumbling upon a mysterious new kid in their neighborhood , Clarence, Jeff and Sumo decide to take the kid out on the town showing him the fun of junk food, arcades and soda! However, this new lifestyle may be more then the new kid bargained for.

added.title: Ballroom
added.description: MG fixes up the ballroom and warns UG and PS not to step a foot in there until he gets a chance to use it.  But UG mistakenly tosses a ball into the room.  Now PS and UG have to retrieve the ball without touching one foot to the ground.

added.title: Big Reveal
added.description: KO finds out who his father is.

added.title: Alien Hunt! With Meteorfire and Cosmos Part 1
added.description: Bumblebee enlists washed-up TV show host Meteorfire to help him find another of Windblade's psychic shards on Luna-3.

added.title: Alien Hunt! With Meteorfire and Cosmos Part 2
added.description: Bumblebee runs the gauntlet of creepily haunted Luna-3, while Meteorfire records everything on camera for his show.

added.title: Thunderhowl Part 1
added.description: Bumblebee and Chromia travel to Crystal City to recover one of Windblade's psychic shards and encounter a long-lost bot.

added.title: Wild Wild Wheel Part 2
added.description: WildWheel finds Optimus Prime rebuilding a small Cybertronian town, only to discover the Prime does not recognize him.

added.title: Wild Wild Wheel Part 1
added.description: A dangerous lone gunslinger named WildWheel returns to Cybertron looking for Optimus Prime.

added.title: Thunderhowl Part 2
added.description: Released after eons of imprisonment, Thunderhowl helps Bee and Chromia navigate the dangerous Crystal City.

added.title: Super Sweet 6
added.description: Morbucks throws the biggest birthday party of all time, and Blossom is the only one not invited.

added.title: The Tell Tale Schedulebot
added.description: After Blossom and Buttercup break Schedulebot, they'll do anything to keep the truth from coming out.

added.title: Plaza Alone
added.description: It's KO's birthday, and Rad and Enid want to make sure everything goes perfectly.

added.title: Plaza Abandonada
added.description: Es el cumpleaños de KO, y Rad y Enid quieren asegurarse de que todo salga a la perfección.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Eres El Asistente De Todos
added.description: Para demostrarle a Enid que ser útil es gratificante, K.O. ayuda a la gente en toda Plaza Lakewood Turbo.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: You're Everybody's Sidekick
added.description: KO sets out to prove to Enid that being helpful is rewarding by helping people all around the Lakewood Plaza Turbo.

added.title: Trouble Helix
added.description: Flashback episode: Young Ben, Gwen, and Grandpa Max visit Azmuth on Galvan Prime. There, they have their first encounter with Malware, a corrupted Mechamorph who's determined to make Azmuth cure him, by any means!

added.title: El Relopulpo
added.description: En una pacífica ciudad costera, Ben no solo debe enfrentarse a Vapor Smythe -su arcaico antagonista- y a su última creación, el Relopulpo... isino que también debe enfrentarse a su temor más profundo y oscuro: los calamares!

added.title: Jethro Es Tuyo
added.description: iK.O. consigue su primera misión en solitario!
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Jethro's All Yours
added.description: KO gets his first solo mission!

added.title: Toma 10
added.description: Mientras Ben intenta rodar su propia película independiente, por accidente libera a una pandilla de insectos y, cuando la lucha se traslada a su guarida oculta, Ben debe enfrentarse a su líder narcisista: La Hormiga Reina.

added.title: Jamas Confies en un Humano
added.description: Mientras Aspheera busca vengarse del "Engañador Traicionero" que la traicionó, el ninja hace un sorprendente descubrimiento.

added.title: Sitiados
added.description: Habiendo aprendido que el Maestro Wu es el "Traicionero", los ninja se encuentran asediados en el Monasterio, tratando de proteger a Wu de la ira de Aspheera.

added.title: Fathers and Friends/Midsummer Nightmare
added.description: Midsummer Nightmare: Drago and the other AO Bakugan face an unseen threat with earth shattering power only to be left wondering if it was all a dream./Father's and Fiends: Osamu Kazami comes to take his son Shun back home and finds a defiance he hadn't counted on.

added.title: El Club de Exploradores
added.description: El ninja debe entrar en el Club del Explorador para obtener el segundo Pergamino de Spinjitzu Prohibido, en conflicto con el gerente del club y los miembros furiosos del club.

added.title: Perdidos en la Cloaca
added.description: Craig acepta ayudar a la Reina de las Alcantarillas a trazar el mapa de las alcantarillas, pero rápidamente se encuentra en una situación que lo supera.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Dawn Before Dusk
added.description: Dawn Before Dusk, Part 1: The AO meet Benton Dusk discovering that their quiet little corner of the world is about to become much, much larger./Dawn Before Dusk, Part 2: Benton Dusk reveals that the AO have been indentified as persons of interest by powerful corporations including Philomena Dusk's AAAnimus.

added.title: La Venganza es Mia
added.description: Aspheera llega al Monasterio de Spinjitzu y se enfrenta a Wu, obligando a uno de los ninjas a hacer un sacrificio heroico.

added.title: El futuro es de Carton
added.description: Los niños conocen a un excéntrico Creador de Cartón que invita a Craig a ayudarlo a terminar su obra maestra.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: Stratified/Maze Daze
added.description: Stratified: The AO embark on a mission into the mysterious labyrinth world of Vestroia to find Strata the Hunter and free the Bakugan he has imprisoned./Maze Daze: Lost in the maze of Vestroia the AO encounter powerful forces that seem to be struggling for control over the alien landscape.

added.title: Una Fria Despedida
added.description: Habiendo aprendido que Zane no está muerto, el Maestro Wu se prepara para ir tras él, pero Lloyd y el otro ninja toman el asunto en sus propias manos y desafían a su Maestro.

added.title: La Camada
added.description: La determinación de Craig de conseguirle a su abuelo un caparazón de cigarra hace que él, Kelsey y JP queden atrapados en su tronco.
added.originalseriesname: Craig of the Creek en Espanol

added.title: All Jungled Up/Outer Demons
added.description: All Jungled Up: Still lost in Vestroia the AO experience mind altering effects of the nearby Core Cell and come face to face with the Bakuzon monster Tiko./Outer Demons: The AO find the doorway out of Vestroia only to learn they have entered a mirror world of their own imagining created by the Core Cell.

added.title: Matter of the Mind/Core Cell
added.description: Matter of Mind: Drago leads the Bakugan against the threat of Tiko to protect a powerful energy source called the Core Cell./Core Cell: The AO defend the Core Cell from an attack by Tiko and in a last ditch effort to save it Dan manages to evolve Drago into his L2 form.

added.title: Pesadilla de Verano
added.description: Drago y los otros Bakugan de Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a una nueva y poderosa amenaza, solo para dejarlos preguntándose si todo habrá sido un sueño.

added.title: Padres y Amigos
added.description: Osamu Kazami viene para llevarse a su hijo Shun a casa y se encuentra con un obstáculo que no había contemplado.

added.title: Vilgax Must Croak
added.description: Ben and Rook escort Vilgax to a maximum-security prison planet, but the Incurseans have other plans. (Introducing Eighteight.)

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 1
added.description: Los Fantásticos conocen a Benton Dusk y descubren que su pequeño mundo está a punto de volverse mucho más grande.

added.title: Industrias Dusk Parte 2
added.description: Benton Dusk revela que Los Fantásticos son considerados personas de interés por poderosas corporaciones como AAAnimus.

added.title: This Man, This Man Man!
added.description: When Guts Man goes on a ravenous rampage across the city, Mega Man must turn to an unlikely ally, Man Man, a bumbling DIY human analog to our hero.

added.title: Stratificados
added.description: Los Fantásticos emprenden una misión en el misterioso mundo laberíntico de Vestroia para buscar a Strata El Cazador y liberar a los Bakugan que tiene presos.

added.title: A Guilded Cage
added.description: Mega Man must stop Namagem and an army of hypnotized Good Guild bots from breaking into Dr. Light's lab.

added.title: Aventura en el Laberinto
added.description: Perdidos en el laberinto de Vestroia, Los Fantásticos se enfrentan a poderosas fuerzas que parecen luchar por el control del planeta.

added.title: To Air Is Robot
added.description: Air Man stakes a claim on the skies above Silicon City, threatening anything that trespasses on his airspace.

added.title: Atrapados en la Jungla
added.description: Aún perdidos en Vestroia, Los Fantásticos experimentan los efectos de la Célula Núcleo que altera sus cuerpos, y se encuentran cara a cara con el monstruo Bakugan, Tiko.

added.title: Watt's Happening?!
added.description: When Elec Man derails the school play by hijacking Silicon Central's power, Aki/Mega Man must use what he has learned onstage to defeat his supercharged foe.

added.title: Demonios Internos
added.description: Los Fantásticos encuentran la forma de salir de Vestroia, pero descubren que en realidad están en un mundo paralelo.

added.title: Chill Out, Bruh
added.description: Aki and Suna take a rehabilitated Ice Man out for a day in the city, but things take a turn for the worse as he misinterprets their cues and turns a game of hover hockey into a literal freeze out!

added.title: Una Extrana Conexion
added.description: Drago lidera a los Bakugan contra la amenaza de Tiko, para proteger una poderosa fuente de energía.

added.title: La Celula Nucleo
added.description: Los Fantásticos defienden la Célula Núcleo de un ataque de Tiko, y en el último intento de Dan por salvarla, él y Drago logran liberar un nuevo poder.

added.title: Vreedlemania
added.description: Pa Vreedle reunites with Ma for all-out destruction.

added.title: Separacion
added.description: Adorabat siente que es dejada de lado y desea que Mao Mao y Colosal pasen menos tiempo juntos y más tiempo con ella. Pero cuando el deseo de Adorabat se hace realidad y destruye la amistad de Mao Mao y Colosal, solo el secreto de su pasado podrá volver a unirlos.

added.title: La Aventura de la Moto de Mao Mao
added.description: Cuando Mao Mao subestima por igual a sus enemigos y a sus amigos, por poco le cuesta el reino entero.

added.title: Ultracolosal
added.description: Colosal se vuelve enorme para destruir a un monstruo altísimo, pero cuando se rehúsa a volver a su tamaño normal, el reino se enfrenta a un nuevo terror… el apetito insaciable de Colosal.

added.title: Ola de Calor
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín tratan de esparcir alegría durante una ola de calor en toda la ciudad.

added.title: Falafel en la Carcel
added.description: Manzana y Cebollín deben sacar a Falafel de la cárcel por un delito que no cometió.

added.title: La Aventura Perfecta
added.description: Cuando a Mao Mao se le antoja vivir la aventura perfecta, Adorabat dice una mentira piadosa.

added.title: Sin Atajos
added.description: Tras esforzarse por mantener el ritmo en las batallas, Adorabat consigue una armadura cibernética. ¿Pero podrán unos nuevos y sofisticados poderes compensar la falta de experiencia?

added.title: Rio de Oro
added.description: Manzana y Cebolla intentan terminar un cuento antes de que el libro desaparezca para siempre.

added.title: Babysitting Bedlam/Rubbed the Wrong Way
added.description: Rubbed the Wrong Way: After a Bakugan field errupts the town kids stampede to get their own Bakugan but when the field is contaminated Lia must save the day./Babysitting Bedlam: Dan and Wynton meet a strange boy who leads them into an underground maze where they discover the boy's Bakugan has been enslaved.

added.title: Mask of Power/Story Holes
added.description:
Mask of Power: Philomena Dusk from AAAnimus Corp. hires Magnus and gives him a control implant to bolster the power of his Bakugan to defeat Dan./Story Holes:  
A cryptic call leads the AO in search of a missing Bakugan but they soon realize the call was actually a test from a mysterious benefactor.

added.title: Home on the Run/Top Slot
added.description: Home on the Run: We are introduced to Shun's mysterious backstory, his relationship with his industrialist father and desire for a closer knit family./Top Slot: Dan and Shun butt heads on how best to make the AO a real team amidst growing threats including the mysterious Shargo Ronin.

added.title: The End of the Universe III Part 1
added.description: Windblade wakes the War Titan Iaconus, only to discover the Quintessons have a Titan of their own!

added.title: The End of the Universe III Part 2
added.description: Iaconus and Croaton do battle as Optimus, Bumblebee and Wheeljack contend with the Scientist.

added.title: The End of the Universe IV Part 1
added.description: With Iaconus down, the Cybertronians make a desperate last stand against Judge Starscream.

added.title: The End of the Universe IV Part 2
added.description: Megatron returns from the Multiverse with enough new found powers to contest Judge Starscream, Windblade uses all her power attempting to free Croaton from Quintesson control.

added.title: Enemy Line Part 1
added.description: While Optimus struggles to be a leader in peace-time, Bumblebee undertakes a daring mission into Decepticon territory.

added.title: Enemy Line Part 2
added.description: Bee recovers a comatose Windblade from Shadowstriker and must shepherd her safely from Decepticon territory.

added.title: Goat!
added.description: Prohyas becomes obsessed with riding an uncooperative goat to get over a mountain.

added.title: Equipo Monstruo
added.description: Los Titanes quieren convertirse en los mejores del pueblo a la hora de pedir dulces o trucos en Halloween y, para ello, Raven lanza un hechizo que los convierte en monstruos reales.

added.title: Halloween vs. Navidad
added.description: Cuando Santa Claus intenta apoderarse de Halloween, los Titanes necesitan a un par de espíritus para detenerlo.

added.title: Concurso de Disfraces
added.description: Hartos de que los Hive Five les ganen en el concurso de disfraces, los Titanes elaboran un plan para ganar.

added.title: La Suciedad
added.description: A Ben le encargan la tarea de limpiar la Chatarra, pero cuando, engañado por los viles villanos Fly Guys, permite que se lo roben, debe perseguirlos antes de que fabriquen una larva monstruosa imparable con un objetivo claro: destruir Las Vegas.

added.title: Filtro Acuatico
added.description: El viaje de Ben, Gwen y Max a las Cataratas del Niágara se ve interrumpido por los horribles Hydromanders: unas criaturas que los amenazan a ellos y a los demás turistas.

added.title: El Lider Del Ring
added.description: Cuando Ben tiene una racha ganadora en un videojuego, se le ocurre una idea para ganar un partido real de lucha, hasta que un luchador intimidante decide convertirlo en un verdadero desafío.

added.title: Sobreviviendo A La Tormenta
added.description: El campamento de Ben y Gwen se ve interrumpido por los gélidos Weatherheads -Gust-o, Hail-o, & Shock-o-, pero un Omnitrix que funciona mal y dispara un montón de extraterrestres podría no ser un pronóstico de éxito.

added.title: Las Noticias Nunca Duermen
added.description: Lil 'Nelson toma un trabajo como repartidor de periódicos, lo cual es más difícil de lo que parece en una ciudad invadida por Pyro Vipers y una malvada hechicera serpentina.

added.title: Ninja Contra Lava
added.description: Los ninja se encuentran atrapados en una pirámide y deben escapar de la lava invasora para advertir a la ciudad de NINJAGO de una nueva invasión serpentina.

added.title: Serpientastrofe
added.description: El ataque de Serpentine en NINJAGO City se ve desde una perspectiva inesperada, completamente al estilo de un noticiero en vivo entregado por Gayle Gossip y su camarógrafo.

added.title: Impotente
added.description: El ninja corre al Museo de Historia de NINJAGO para recuperar un pergamino peligroso antes de que caiga en manos de la Hechicera Serpentina Aspheera.

added.title: Historia Antigua
added.description: Mientras Aspheera busca vengarse del "Engañador Traicionero" que la traicionó, el ninja hace un sorprendente descubrimiento.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: Cuando, luego de un accidente reciente, Nom Nom aparece en la entrada de la casa de los Osos, desaliñado y destronado de su puesto como la estrella más tierna de Internet de la historia, consigue la ayuda de los Osos para tratar de recuperar su título.

added.title: Una Necesidad Inquietante
added.description: La aparición de un nuevo campo Bakugan hace que los chicos del pueblo corran a buscar a sus propios Bakugan. Pero cuando el campo es contaminado, Lia debe salvarlos a todos.

added.title: Tutores Bakugan
added.description: Dan y Wynton conocen a un extraño chico que los lleva a un laberinto subterráneo, donde descubren que el Bakugan del chico ha sido esclavizado.

added.title: Mascara de Poder
added.description: Philomena Dusk, de la Corporación AAAnimus, contrata a Magnus y le implanta un dispositivo que aumenta el poder de su Bakugan para derrotar a Dan.

added.title: Una Verdad a Medias
added.description: Un críptico correo electrónico lleva a Los Fantásticos en busca de un Bakugan desaparecido, pero pronto se dan cuenta de que el correo era una prueba de un misterioso benefactor.

added.title: Charlie Y La Serpiente
added.description: Charlie (alias Pie Grande) es un tipo solitario a quien, como a los Osos, le gustaría encontrar un lugar en el mundo. En su intento por conseguirlo, Charlie organiza una fiesta, pero termina embarcándose en una aventura con el más improbable de los animales: una serpiente salvaje.

added.title: Huyendo de Casa
added.description: Descubriremos el misterioso pasado de Shun, su relación con su padre (un magnate de la industria), y su deseo por tener una familia más unida.

added.title: Un Verdadero Lider
added.description: Entre diversas amenazas, como el misterioso Shargo Ronin, Dan y Shun no pueden acordar la mejor forma de convertir a Los Fantásticos en un verdadero equipo.

added.title: Hibernacion
added.description: Por ser un grupo urbano, los Osos jamás escucharon hablar de la idea de hibernar, hasta que Chloe les cuenta al respecto. Pardo, a quien le encanta la idea de comer mucho y luego dormir todo lo que se le dé la gana, se entrega a la hibernación sin pensarlo. Pero está tan entusiasmado con la idea de hibernar... que no se puede dormir.

added.title: El terror en la Montana Hook
added.description: Tigro lleva a León-O a la cima de la Montaña Hook para enseñarle una lección sobre la confianza. Pero cuando quedan atrapados por una tormenta de nieve y se refugian en una espeluznante cabaña propiedad del espeluznante Snowman, lo que se pondrá a prueba es la capacidad de Tigro para confiar.

added.title: Venganza apestosa
added.description: Cuando una mofeta viene a buscar su venganza anual contra el Chef, Duncan ve una oportunidad de tomarse unas vacaciones de la guardería.

added.title: La Espada Perdida
added.description: A León-O le recuerdan que debe conectar la Espada del Augurio al Cubil Felino todas las noches o la base se quedará sin energía. No hay problema, no es que León-O vaya a perder accidentalmente la espada o algo así, ¿verdad?

removed.title: The Gilded Path
removed.description: The headquarters to the resistance is breached and Lloyd scrambles to avoid capture. Meanwhile, the Ninja are caught by Heavy Metal, but find an unlikely ally.

removed.title: Rush to Greatness
removed.description: Rush puts his new battle upgrades to the test in a battle with Wave Man.

removed.title: Shun and Lightning/Premonition of a Storm
removed.description: Shun and Lightning: Shun and Lightning are on the hunt for a rare Tumpee, when they run into McQ! With all the devices related crimes happening in Los Volmos, Shun decides to investigate to try to get to the bottom of McQ's nefarious dealings./Premonition of a Storm: After a run in with McQ, Shun and Lightning find themselves in a little bit trouble. They're trapped!  Tied up with no Bakugan to help them escape, and no one knows their whereabouts. It will take some big help to help them get out of this mess.

removed.title: Swish
removed.description: Namagem attacks Mega Man using a variety of powers, revealing that they both can replicate schematics. However, Namagem can carry more than three at a time! The true beginning of the mysterious villain's arc begins here.

removed.title: Firstbourne
removed.description: Emperor Garmadon has taken control of Ninjago City where Lloyd retreats to the shadows. Meanwhile, the other Ninja and Young Wu are shipwrecked in the Realm of Oni & Dragon and find they are not alone.

removed.title: Minus Mini
removed.description: When Mega Mini is kidnapped by Blasto Woman, Mega Man must track down his missing partner without the full use of his own systems.

removed.title: Wynton's Reality Show/Bakugan Soccer
removed.description: Wynton's Reality Show: Lia has had it with Wynton's pranking, but little does she know Wynton is in for a taste of his own medicine. A prank goes too far, and Wynton finds himself in a real-life nightmare with a rampaging Bakugan!/Bakugan Soccer: The Awesome Brawlers and their Bakugan decide to have a game of Bakugan Soccer! The intensity ramps up when Pepe, his teammates and a mysterious coach show up for a little fun. It will take major teamwork for the Awesome Brawlers Bakugan to defeat this rowdy bunch.

removed.title: Radio Ninjago libre
removed.description: Lloyd deberá encontrar su voz mientras lidera una pequeña resistencia para capturar las señales de transmisión en Ciudad Ninjago. Mientras tanto en el Primer Reino, el Barón de Hierro lleva a los Ninjas en una cacería de dragones.
removed.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

removed.title: A Cut Above
removed.description: Aki and Bert accidentally damage a bonsai tree outside the Lighthouse, sending the Lights' perfectionist gardener on a slicing-and-dicing spree as Cut Man.

removed.title: How to Build a Dragon
removed.description: While Lloyd and the rebels celebrate their successful strike against Emperor Garmadon, in the Realm of Oni and Dragon, the Ninja dare an elaborate escape from the clutches of Iron Baron and his Dragon Hunters.

removed.title: A Bot and His Dog
removed.description: Tired of fielding of low stakes house calls, Mega Man gets what he wishes for when Hypno Woman hijacks the local power plant.

removed.title: Lost Sword
removed.description: Lion-O is reminded that he needs to plug the Sword of Omens into the Cats' Lair each night or else the base will run out of power. That's fine, it's not like Lion-O's going to accidentally lose the sword or anything. Right?

removed.title: Hierro y piedra
removed.description: Cole y Wu Joven intentan liberar a sus amigos, que han sido capturados por una tribu de Cazadores de Dragones. Mientras tanto en Ninjago, Lloyd se reúne con unos viejos amigos que quizás sean aliados valiosos contra el Emperador Garmadon.
removed.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

removed.title: El camino dorado
removed.description: El cuartel general de la resistencia es irrumpido y Lloyd lucha por no ser capturado. Mientras tanto, los Ninjas son capturados por Heavy-Metal, pero encuentran un aliado improbable.
removed.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

removed.title: Como construir un dragon
removed.description: Mientras Lloyd y los rebeldes celebran su exitoso golpe contra el Emperador Garmadon, en el Reino de Oni y Dragón, los Ninjas se aventuran con un elaborado escape de las garras del Barón de Hierro y sus Cazadores de Dragones.
removed.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

removed.title: Primogenita
removed.description: El Emperador Garmadon ha tomado el control de Ciudad Ninjago donde Lloyd se retira hacia las sombras. Mientras tanto, los otros Ninjas y Wu Joven quedan varados en el Reino de Oni y Dragón y descubren que no están solos.
removed.originalseriesname: Ninjago: Masters of Spinjitzu en Espanol

removed.title: Radio Free NinjaGo
removed.description: Lloyd must find his voice as he leads a small resistance to capture the airwaves in Ninjago City. Meanwhile in the First Realm, Iron Baron takes the Ninja on a dragon hunt.

removed.title: Iron & Stone
removed.description: Cole and Young Wu attempt to free their friends, who have been taken captive by a tribe of Dragon Hunters. Meanwhile in Ninjago, Lloyd is reunited with some old friends who may prove valuable allies against Emperor Garmadon.
